N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 133.1 - Definitions

State Regulations

As used in this article: (a) Name or mark means any word, name, symbol, picture, design or any combination thereof, produced upon and used by a
person to indicate ownership of carts, cases, trays, baskets, boxes and other
containers. (b) Person means any
individual, firm, partnership, corporation, association, union or other
organization. (c) Permanently
affixed means branded, stamped, stenciled, engraved, etched, blown, embossed, impressed, or otherwise permanently placed upon any cart, case, tray, basket, box or other container. Notes
